The defendant Amber L Plate was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Criminal Damage to Property, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).
  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Amber L Plate in court with attorney Thomas Paul Alberti.  Irene Elizabeth Parthum appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  

Sentencing proceeded.    Statements made by counsel and defendant.  Additional statement by Lennys G.  

AS TO THE AMENDED COUNT 1:
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 9 months in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 58 days time served, Huber privileges for work and treatment.  

AS TO THE AMENDED COUNT 2:
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 9 months in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 0 days time served, Huber privileges for work and treatment.  

AS TO BOTH COUNTS:
The last 6 months, Huber privileges for work, treatment, The Day Reporting Center and electonic monitoring. 

The court STAYED the sentences and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 18 months with the following conditions:  

*Mental health assessment and comply with any treatment deemed necessary by the department.
*Alcohol and drug assessment and comply with any treatment deemed necessary by the department.
*Absolute sobriety.
*Random urine screens.  No positive results.
*No illegal drugs.
*No controlled substances without valid prescription.
*No contact with drug community.
*No contact with the victim Lennys G.
*Seek and maintain full time employment.
*Cognitive Behavior Therapy.

Restitution is ordered in the amount of $529.67 to be paid to Lennys G.

- No DNA sample and no DNA surcharge is ordered, this case predates the change in law.
- Pay all costs, fees and surcharges,  collected by DOC out of up to 25% of any applicable prison funds and wages, during any period of ES.  To be paid by the end of probation.  If not paid, a civil judgment to be entered.
